# H: Drive Only — ABSOLUTE RULE

```txt
Project Storage ≠ Cursor Internal Storage
```

**Goal: Zero project assets on C:.** (Not zero bytes on C: — Cursor keeps IDE metadata there.)

**All project work on H:.** No exceptions.

## Before EVERY Command

Burt MUST run first:

```powershell
cd H:\FoundryOS
.\scripts\setup-h-drive.ps1
node scripts/enforce-h-drive.js
```

Or use the wrapper:

```powershell
.\scripts\run-on-h.ps1 npm run build
```

## Enforced Paths (H: ONLY)

| Resource | Path |
|----------|------|
| Project root | `H:\FoundryOS` |
| node_modules | `H:\FoundryOS\node_modules` |
| npm cache | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\npm` |
| turbo cache | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\turbo` |
| temp | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\temp` |
| build/next | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\build` |
| netlify | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\netlify` |
| supabase local | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\supabase` |
| git repo | `H:\FoundryOS\.git` |

## Forbidden

- `C:\Users\...\AppData\Local\npm-cache` for this project
- `C:\Users\...\AppData\Local\Temp` for builds
- `C:\FoundryOS` or any C: clone
- Running npm/git/build from any directory other than `H:\FoundryOS`

## If C: Gets Polluted

```powershell
.\scripts\full-c-drive-migration.ps1
# or: npm run migrate:c-to-h
npm run verify:c-clean
```

Mirrors Cursor metadata to `H:\FoundryOS\.cursor\cursor-mirror\`, sends redundant C: copies to Recycle Bin.

## Violation Response

1. **STOP** the command
2. Run `cleanup-c-drive-foundry.ps1`
3. Re-run from `H:\FoundryOS` with `setup-h-drive.ps1`
4. Never apologize and continue on C: — fix it first

## Note on Cursor IDE

Cursor keeps a small IDE shell at `C:\Users\User\.cursor\projects\h-FoundryOS\` (MCP descriptors, terminals). That is NOT the project. The project lives at `H:\FoundryOS`. Burt never puts code, node_modules, builds, or caches on C:.
